The paper deals with performance analysis of subspace algorithms for parameter estimation, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI). The use of Vandermonde matrices and Hilbert's inequality suggests a numerical analysis (cs.NA) perspective. The focus on deterministic, finite sample size, and finite-SNR performance analysis suggests a systems and control (cs.SY) perspective. Finally, the use of upper bounds and inequalities suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) perspective.
